== PER (주가수익비율) ==
* P/E ratio; Price/Earnings Ratio
* Ratio of a company's stock price to the company's earnings per share (EPS)
* PER이 높으면 고평가, 낮으면 저평가(?)  사실은 그 반대의 성향; 
* '''PER''': more growth potential as perceived by investors (성장가능성)

** how much investors are willing to pay per doallar of earnings
* Sector마다 PER 값들이 꽤 다름

== PBR (주가순자산비율) ==
* P/B Ratio; Price-to-Book Ratio; Priice-Equity Ratio 
* [[http://merrow.tistory.com/451]], [[https://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/price-to-bookratio.asp]]
* PBR = 시가총액/순자산
** 회사의 자산 = 순자산 + 부채
* PBR이 높으면 고평가, 낮으면 저평가

